---
import ServiceLayout from '../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const title = "Paint Protection Film Fort Lauderdale | Mobile Service | Route95";
const description = "Professional paint protection film (PPF) in Fort Lauderdale. Clear film protects against rock chips and debris. Premium XPEL film. Call 754-215-2272";

const parentCategory = {
  href: `${base}car-detailing-services-fort-lauderdale/`,
  title: "Car Detailing Services"
};
---

<ServiceLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  h1="Paint Protection Film Fort Lauderdale"
  intro="Paint protection film (PPF) is a clear, self-healing film that shields your paint from rock chips, road debris, and minor abrasions."
  currentPage="/paint-protection-film-fort-lauderdale/"
  parentCategory={parentCategory}
>
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
    <div class="lg:col-span-2 space-y-8">
      <section>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          No matter how careful you are, your car's paint takes hits. Rock chips from highway driving. Door dings in parking lots. Shopping cart scratches. Bug splatter that etches if left too long. Paint protection film takes this punishment instead of your paint.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          We install premium paint protection film on vehicles throughout Fort Lauderdale. Whether you want full vehicle coverage or just high-impact areas like the hood and fenders, we can protect your investment.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          Modern PPF is virtually invisible when installed correctly. It self-heals minor scratches with heat exposure and won't yellow or peel for years.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#0f2a4a] mb-4">How Much Does Paint Protection Film Cost in Fort Lauderdale?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          <strong>Paint protection film in Fort Lauderdale ranges from $500 for partial coverage to $5,000+ for full vehicle wraps, depending on coverage area and film quality.</strong>
        </p>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg mb-4">
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm"><strong>Common coverage options:</strong></p>
          <ul class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-2 space-y-1">
            <li>• Partial front (hood, fenders, mirrors): $800-$1,500</li>
            <li>• Full front (+ bumper, headlights): $1,500-$2,500</li>
            <li>• Full vehicle wrap: $4,000-$7,000+</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          The investment pays off when you avoid a single $1,000+ paint repair from rock chips. Luxury and exotic vehicles benefit most due to expensive paint repair costs.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#0f2a4a] mb-4">How Long Does PPF Installation Take?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          <strong>PPF installation takes 1-4 days depending on coverage area and whether we use pre-cut patterns or custom templates.</strong>
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
          Partial front coverage can often be completed in a day. Full vehicle wraps require several days for proper installation and curing. The film needs time to settle and any moisture to evaporate before the vehicle is ready.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#0f2a4a] mb-4">What Does Paint Protection Film Protect Against?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          <strong>PPF creates a physical barrier between your paint and the world, absorbing impacts that would otherwise damage your clear coat.</strong>
        </p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-[#0f2a4a] mb-2">Road Hazards</h3>
            <ul class="text-gray-600 text-sm space-y-1">
              <li>• Rock chips from highway driving</li>
              <li>• Gravel kicked up by other vehicles</li>
              <li>• Road debris and construction materials</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-[#0f2a4a] mb-2">Environmental Damage</h3>
            <ul class="text-gray-600 text-sm space-y-1">
              <li>• Bug splatter and bird droppings</li>
              <li>• Tree sap and pollen</li>
              <li>• UV rays that fade paint</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-[#0f2a4a] mb-2">Minor Abrasions</h3>
            <ul class="text-gray-600 text-sm space-y-1">
              <li>• Shopping cart scratches</li>
              <li>• Door dings</li>
              <li>• Light brush scratches</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-[#0f2a4a] mb-2">Self-Healing</h3>
            <ul class="text-gray-600 text-sm space-y-1">
              <li>• Light scratches disappear with heat</li>
              <li>• Swirl marks heal themselves</li>
              <li>• Film returns to perfect clarity</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#0f2a4a] mb-4">Who Should Consider PPF?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Paint protection film is ideal for:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-2">
          <li>New car owners who want to keep paint perfect from day one</li>
          <li>Luxury and exotic vehicle owners (expensive paint repairs)</li>
          <li>Anyone who drives on highways frequently</li>
          <li>Lease vehicle drivers (return the car in perfect condition)</li>
          <li>Car enthusiasts who take pride in their paint</li>
          <li>Anyone planning to keep their vehicle long-term</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>

    <aside class="lg:col-span-1">
      <div class="sticky top-24 space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-[#0f2a4a] mb-4">PPF Quick Facts</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-[#c0c7cf] font-bold">$</span>
              <span class="text-gray-600">$500-$7,000+ by coverage</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-[#c0c7cf] mt-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
              </svg>
              <span class="text-gray-600">1-4 days installation</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-[#c0c7cf] mt-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
              </svg>
              <span class="text-gray-600">Self-healing technology</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-[#c0c7cf] mt-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
              </svg>
              <span class="text-gray-600">Virtually invisible</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-[#c0c7cf] mt-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
              </svg>
              <span class="text-gray-600">5-10 year warranty</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-[#0f2a4a] rounded-xl p-6 text-white">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-4">Get a PPF Quote</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm mb-4">
            Contact us to discuss your coverage options and get a custom quote.
          </p>
          <a href="tel:+17542152272" class="btn-accent w-full flex items-center justify-center gap-2">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M3 5a2 2 0 012-2h3.28a1 1 0 01.948.684l1.498 4.493a1 1 0 01-.502 1.21l-2.257 1.13a11.042 11.042 0 005.516 5.516l1.13-2.257a1 1 0 011.21-.502l4.493 1.498a1 1 0 01.684.949V19a2 2 0 01-2 2h-1C9.716 21 3 14.284 3 6V5z" />
            </svg>
            754-215-2272
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-[#0f2a4a] mb-4">Related Services</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li><a href={`${base}luxury-car-detailing-fort-lauderdale/`} class="text-gray-600 hover:text-[#c0c7cf]">Luxury Car Detailing</a></li>
            <li><a href={`${base}car-waxing-fort-lauderdale/`} class="text-gray-600 hover:text-[#c0c7cf]">Car Waxing</a></li>
            <li><a href={`${base}full-detail-fort-lauderdale/`} class="text-gray-600 hover:text-[#c0c7cf]">Full Detail</a></li>
            <li><a href={`${base}headlight-restoration-fort-lauderdale/`} class="text-gray-600 hover:text-[#c0c7cf]">Headlight Restoration</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </div>
</ServiceLayout>
